BayesB is a sampling algorithm based Bayesian approach, which assumes that the prior distribution of variances across markers is a two-component mixture with one component following an inverted chi-square distribution and the other being a point mass at 0 (Meuwissen et al. 2001). It can be summarized as\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
